('required-programming-mini-game', 'cs-for-gameplay', 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Required Programming Mini Game', 'Milestone project brief: Build a simple text or 2D mini-game using clean functions, state, data structures, save/load, and debugging notes. Build a reviewable game prototype that demonstrates the main decisions from Computer Science for Gameplay. Expected evidence includes a playable prototype or isolated mechanic, controls, rules, and tuning notes, and screenshots or a short playtest observation. Keep scope focused so the result can be completed, checked, and explained.', 'This required milestone project turns the surrounding Game Developer topics into a concrete artifact. It gives the learner a clearer target, suggested build path, and review evidence without treating completion as proof of mastery or job readiness.', 39, 'choice', 'cs-for-gameplay', 203, 7, 4, 'beginner', 2, '{"source": "roadmap.sh/game-developer","parentGroup": "cs-for-gameplay","projectPolicy": "required_milestone","projectPurpose": "milestone_practice","projectKind": "game_project","projectScope": "focused_milestone","evidenceRequired": true,"claimLimit": "reviewable_project_evidence_only_not_mastery_or_job_readiness","suggestedSteps": ["define the core loop or mechanic","build the smallest playable slice","test controls and feedback","record tuning decisions"],"expectedEvidence": ["a playable prototype or isolated mechanic","controls, rules, and tuning notes","screenshots or a short playtest observation"],"optionalPractice": false,"milestone": true}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Build a focused Programming Mini Game artifact that demonstrates the main concepts from Computer Science for Gameplay.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, or workflow decisions used in the project.","Validate the project with appropriate evidence such as tests, screenshots, logs, metrics, queries, or review notes.","Document setup, usage, limitations, and at least one follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["A repository, notebook, dashboard, write-up, prototype, or configuration artifact is available for review.","The README or project notes state the project goal, setup steps, usage path, and expected output.","The deliverable includes a playable prototype or isolated mechanic, controls, rules, and tuning notes, and screenshots or a short playtest observation.","The learner records validation evidence such as tests, screenshots, logs, metrics, query results, playtest notes, or manual verification steps.","The review notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one reasonable next improvement."]'::jsonb),
