('optional-ai-level-prototype', 'procedural-content', 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Optional AI and Level Prototype', 'Optional project brief: Build a level with enemy AI, navigation, scripted encounters, and at least one procedural element. Build a small, reviewable game prototype to practice ideas from Procedural Content and Level Design. Expected evidence includes a playable prototype or isolated mechanic, controls, rules, and tuning notes, and screenshots or a short playtest observation. Keep it lightweight; the goal is applied practice and clearer portfolio evidence, not a mandatory milestone.', 'This optional practice project turns the surrounding Game Developer topics into a concrete artifact. It gives the learner a clearer target, suggested build path, and review evidence without treating completion as proof of mastery or job readiness.', 174, 'choice', 'procedural-content', 902, 8, 4, 'intermediate', 9, '{"source": "roadmap.sh/game-developer","parentGroup": "procedural-content","projectPolicy": "optional_practice","projectPurpose": "optional_practice","projectKind": "game_project","projectScope": "small_practice_artifact","evidenceRequired": true,"claimLimit": "reviewable_project_evidence_only_not_mastery_or_job_readiness","suggestedSteps": ["define the core loop or mechanic","build the smallest playable slice","test controls and feedback","record tuning decisions"],"expectedEvidence": ["a playable prototype or isolated mechanic","controls, rules, and tuning notes","screenshots or a short playtest observation"],"optionalPractice": true,"milestone": false}'::jsonb, false, true, '["Build a small AI and Level Prototype artifact to practice selected concepts from Procedural Content and Level Design.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, or workflow decisions used in the project.","Validate the project with appropriate evidence such as tests, screenshots, logs, metrics, queries, or review notes.","Document setup, usage, limitations, and at least one follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["A repository, notebook, dashboard, write-up, prototype, or configuration artifact is available for review.","The README or project notes state the project goal, setup steps, usage path, and expected output.","The deliverable includes a playable prototype or isolated mechanic, controls, rules, and tuning notes, and screenshots or a short playtest observation.","The learner records validation evidence such as tests, screenshots, logs, metrics, query results, playtest notes, or manual verification steps.","The review notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one reasonable next improvement."]'::jsonb),
