('required-online-feature-project', 'game-backend-services', 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Required Online Feature Project', 'Milestone project brief: Build an online feature demo with login or anonymous identity, leaderboard or cloud save, and one multiplayer or backend service integration. Build a reviewable game prototype that demonstrates the main decisions from Game Backend Services. Expected evidence includes a playable prototype or isolated mechanic, controls, rules, and tuning notes, and screenshots or a short playtest observation. Keep scope focused so the result can be completed, checked, and explained.', 'This required milestone project turns the surrounding Game Developer topics into a concrete artifact. It gives the learner a clearer target, suggested build path, and review evidence without treating completion as proof of mastery or job readiness.', 196, 'choice', 'game-backend-services', 1003, 7, 7, 'advanced', 10, '{"source": "roadmap.sh/game-developer","parentGroup": "game-backend-services","projectPolicy": "required_milestone","projectPurpose": "milestone_practice","projectKind": "game_project","projectScope": "focused_milestone","evidenceRequired": true,"claimLimit": "reviewable_project_evidence_only_not_mastery_or_job_readiness","suggestedSteps": ["define the core loop or mechanic","build the smallest playable slice","test controls and feedback","record tuning decisions"],"expectedEvidence": ["a playable prototype or isolated mechanic","controls, rules, and tuning notes","screenshots or a short playtest observation"],"optionalPractice": false,"milestone": true}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Build a focused Online Feature Project artifact that demonstrates the main concepts from Game Backend Services.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, or workflow decisions used in the project.","Validate the project with appropriate evidence such as tests, screenshots, logs, metrics, queries, or review notes.","Document setup, usage, limitations, and at least one follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["A repository, notebook, dashboard, write-up, prototype, or configuration artifact is available for review.","The README or project notes state the project goal, setup steps, usage path, and expected output.","The deliverable includes a playable prototype or isolated mechanic, controls, rules, and tuning notes, and screenshots or a short playtest observation.","The learner records validation evidence such as tests, screenshots, logs, metrics, query results, playtest notes, or manual verification steps.","The review notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one reasonable next improvement."]'::jsonb),
